*Information*
CTF Name: Bandit Level 0 -> Level 1
Profile: OverTheWire
Difficulty: Easy
Description: The purpose of this level is to educate users on how to find and read files

*Content*
1) Connected to new level through using the username bandit1, with the password as the flag from the previous level. (A breakdown of the ssh 
command can be found in level0)
2) Used command 'ls' to list all files in the current directory
3) Used command 'cat readme' to read the file
                  ^     ^
              command   |
                     file name
The ls command is used to list files in a directory. It can be combined with other flags such as -a which will make sure files starting with . will not be
ignored, or -l which will use long listing format.
